          <article class="submission-note">
            <p>
              This website serves as my official portfolio and final report submission. Some supporting
              documents may be updated as the portfolio is finalized.
            </p>
          </article>

          <div class="report-section-grid">
            <article class="report-card">
              <h3>1. Overview of the Practicum Engagement</h3>
              <p>
                I completed my practicum engagement with the City Government of Bi&ntilde;an under the
                Bi&ntilde;an Access Card Management Information System project. The engagement exposed me
                to real workplace tasks related to information system development, database organization,
                module checking, documentation, troubleshooting, and system improvement. The nature of my
                assignments focused on supporting the development and review of system modules, checking
                database-related requirements, assisting in the improvement of views and models, and
                documenting the progress of assigned practicum tasks. My total rendered hours are based on
                my submitted Daily Time Record and practicum journal.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="report-card">
              <h3>2. Presentation of Output</h3>
              <p>
                My practicum output focused on the Bi&ntilde;an Access Card Management Information System.
                The system is intended to support the management of resident records, categories, sectors,
                services and programs, user roles, and related administrative functions. The output
                demonstrates web-based system development, database handling, user interface organization,
                and role-based access features. Screenshots and sample module outputs will be placed in
                the portfolio as the files are finalized.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="report-card">
              <h3>3. Detailed Discussion of Tasks and Assignments Given</h3>
              <p>
                During the practicum, I assisted with tasks related to models, database structure, module
                review, views, controllers, system testing, troubleshooting, and documentation. I also
                worked on checking local setup issues, database connection problems, project structure
                concerns, and deployment preparation. These tasks helped me understand how system
                development is performed in a real office environment and how each part of the system must
                be reviewed carefully before use.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="report-card">
              <h3>4. Synthesis of the Practicum Engagement</h3>
              <p>
                The practicum engagement helped me understand the importance of proper documentation,
                database organization, teamwork, user roles, testing, and clear communication. I learned
                that system development is not only about writing code but also about solving problems,
                checking details, following standards, and making sure the system supports the actual
                needs of the office.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="report-card">
              <h3>5. Realization and Conclusion</h3>
              <p>
                I realized that an IT practicum requires patience, responsibility, and the ability to
                adapt to real workplace tasks. The experience improved my confidence in troubleshooting,
                documentation, and understanding how information systems are used in a government office
                setting. Overall, the practicum helped prepare me for future IT-related work by giving me
                practical experience in system development and workplace collaboration.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>

